I usually leave a lot of personal stuff off here, but I thought this one was important for all those who know my Dad.  Anyone who has dealt with a parent or loved one going through any type of dimentia, Alzheimer’s, or anything of the sort knows how helpless it feels to watch someone who raised you seem to slip away right in front of your eyes.

It can feel like the person you knew doesn’t exist anymore. It makes you wonder if they even know who you are still. BUT I will tell you walking through that door tonight and watching my dad tear up at the sight of his grandson was something I’ll never forget. 

It was a dinner with few words but I know he was present tonight. My dad hasn’t spoken any words for years now. But when we left he hugged us both tight and found a way to whisper an I love you. Those three words will sit with both of us forever and I know personally it will be a Christmas dinner I’ll never forget. 

We love you too, Dad. 💙
Oh Davis St how far you’ve come!! 🏚️🔜🏢
